113struct ImBitVector; // Store 1-bit per value
114struct ImRect; // An axis-aligned rectangle (2 points)
115struct ImDrawDataBuilder; // Helper to build a ImDrawData instance
116struct ImDrawListSharedData; // Data shared between all ImDrawList instances
117struct ImGuiColorMod; // Stacked color modifier, backup of modified data so we can restore it
118struct ImGuiContext; // Main Dear ImGui context
119struct ImGuiContextHook; // Hook for extensions like ImGuiTestEngine
120struct ImGuiDataTypeInfo; // Type information associated to a ImGuiDataType enum
121struct ImGuiDockContext; // Docking system context
122struct ImGuiDockRequest; // Docking system dock/undock queued request
123struct ImGuiDockNode; // Docking system node (hold a list of Windows OR two child dock nodes)
124struct ImGuiDockNodeSettings; // Storage for a dock node in .ini file (we preserve those even if the associated dock node isn't active during the session)
125struct ImGuiGroupData; // Stacked storage data for BeginGroup()/EndGroup()
126struct ImGuiInputTextState; // Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
127struct ImGuiLastItemData; // Status storage for last submitted items
128struct ImGuiMenuColumns; // Simple column measurement, currently used for MenuItem() only
129struct ImGuiNavItemData; // Result of a gamepad/keyboard directional navigation move query result
130struct ImGuiMetricsConfig; // Storage for ShowMetricsWindow() and DebugNodeXXX() functions
131struct ImGuiNextWindowData; // Storage for SetNextWindow** functions
132struct ImGuiNextItemData; // Storage for SetNextItem** functions
133struct ImGuiOldColumnData; // Storage data for a single column for legacy Columns() api
134struct ImGuiOldColumns; // Storage data for a columns set for legacy Columns() api
135struct ImGuiPopupData; // Storage for current popup stack
136struct ImGuiSettingsHandler; // Storage for one type registered in the .ini file
137struct ImGuiStackSizes; // Storage of stack sizes for debugging/asserting
138struct ImGuiStyleMod; // Stacked style modifier, backup of modified data so we can restore it
139struct ImGuiTabBar; // Storage for a tab bar
140struct ImGuiTabItem; // Storage for a tab item (within a tab bar)
141struct ImGuiTable; // Storage for a table
142struct ImGuiTableColumn; // Storage for one column of a table
143struct ImGuiTableInstanceData; // Storage for one instance of a same table
144struct ImGuiTableTempData; // Temporary storage for one table (one per table in the stack), shared between tables.
145struct ImGuiTableSettings; // Storage for a table .ini settings
146struct ImGuiTableColumnsSettings; // Storage for a column .ini settings
147struct ImGuiWindow; // Storage for one window
148struct ImGuiWindowTempData; // Temporary storage for one window (that's the data which in theory we could ditch at the end of the frame, in practice we currently keep it for each window)
149struct ImGuiWindowSettings; // Storage for a window .ini settings (we keep one of those even if the actual window wasn't instanced during this session)

212//#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_IO IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG // Enable log

224// "Paranoid" Debug Asserts are meant to only be enabled during specific debugging/work, otherwise would slow down the code too much.
225// We currently don't have many of those so the effect is currently negligible, but onward intent to add more aggressive ones in the code.
226//#define IMGUI_DEBUG_PARANOID
227#ifdef IMGUI_DEBUG_PARANOID
228#define IM_ASSERT_PARANOID(_EXPR) IM_ASSERT(_EXPR)
229#else
230#define IM_ASSERT_PARANOID(_EXPR)
231#endif

233// Error handling
234// Down the line in some frameworks/languages we would like to have a way to redirect those to the programmer and recover from more faults.
235#ifndef IM_ASSERT_USER_ERROR
236#define IM_ASSERT_USER_ERROR(_EXP,_MSG) IM_ASSERT((_EXP) && _MSG) // Recoverable User Error
237#endif

242#define IM_NEWLINE "\r\n" // Play it nice with Windows users (Update: since 2018-05, Notepad finally appears to support Unix-style carriage returns!)
243#else
244#define IM_NEWLINE "\n"
245#endif
246#define IM_TABSIZE (4)
247#define IM_MEMALIGN(_OFF,_ALIGN) (((_OFF) + ((_ALIGN) - 1)) & ~((_ALIGN) - 1)) // Memory align e.g. IM_ALIGN(0,4)=0, IM_ALIGN(1,4)=4, IM_ALIGN(4,4)=4, IM_ALIGN(5,4)=8
248#define IM_F32_TO_INT8_UNBOUND(_VAL) ((int)((_VAL) * 255.0f + ((_VAL)>=0 ? 0.5f : -0.5f))) // Unsaturated, for display purpose
249#define IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(_VAL) ((int)(ImSaturate(_VAL) * 255.0f + 0.5f)) // Saturated, always output 0..255
250#define IM_FLOOR(_VAL) ((float)(int)(_VAL)) // ImFloor() is not inlined in MSVC debug builds
251#define IM_ROUND(_VAL) ((float)(int)((_VAL) + 0.5f)) //

267// Debug Tools
268// Use 'Metrics/Debugger->Tools->Item Picker' to break into the call-stack of a specific item.
269// This will call IM_DEBUG_BREAK() which you may redefine yourself. See https://github.com/scottt/debugbreak for more reference.
270#ifndef IM_DEBUG_BREAK
271#if defined (_MSC_VER)
272#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __debugbreak()
273#elif defined(__clang__)
274#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __builtin_debugtrap()
275#elif defined(__GNUC__) && (defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__))
276#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile("int $0x03")
277#elif defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__thumb__)
278#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile(".inst 0xde01")
279#elif defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__arm__) && !defined(__thumb__)
280#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile(".inst 0xe7f001f0");
281#else
282#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() IM_ASSERT(0) // It is expected that you define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() into something that will break nicely in a debugger!
283#endif
284#endif // #ifndef IM_DEBUG_BREAK

316static inline void ImQsort(void* base, size_t count, size_t size_of_element, int(IMGUI_CDECL *compare_func)(void const*, void const*)) { if (count > 1) qsort(base, count, size_of_element, compare_func); }

322// Helpers: Bit manipulation
323static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(int v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
324static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(ImU64 v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
325static inline int ImUpperPowerOfTwo(int v) { v--; v |= v >> 1; v |= v >> 2; v |= v >> 4; v |= v >> 8; v |= v >> 16; v++; return v; }

362// Helpers: ImVec2/ImVec4 operators
363// We are keeping those disabled by default so they don't leak in user space, to allow user enabling implicit cast operators between ImVec2 and their own types (using IM_VEC2_CLASS_EXTRA etc.)
364// We unfortunately don't have a unary- operator for ImVec2 because this would needs to be defined inside the class itself.
365#ifdef IMGUI_DEFINE_MATH_OPERATORS
366IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_OFF
367static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs, lhs.y * rhs); }
368static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs, lhs.y / rhs); }
369static inline ImVec2 operator+(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y); }
370static inline ImVec2 operator-(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y); }
371static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }
372static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs.x, lhs.y / rhs.y); }
373static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs; lhs.y *= rhs; return lhs; }
374static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs; lhs.y /= rhs; return lhs; }
375static inline ImVec2& operator+=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x += rhs.x; lhs.y += rhs.y; return lhs; }
376static inline ImVec2& operator-=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x -= rhs.x; lhs.y -= rhs.y; return lhs; }
377static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs.x; lhs.y *= rhs.y; return lhs; }
378static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs.x; lhs.y /= rhs.y; return lhs; }
379static inline ImVec4 operator+(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y, lhs.z + rhs.z, lhs.w + rhs.w); }
380static inline ImVec4 operator-(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y, lhs.z - rhs.z, lhs.w - rhs.w); }
381static inline ImVec4 operator*(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y, lhs.z * rhs.z, lhs.w * rhs.w); }
382IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_RESTORE
383#endif

407// Helpers: Maths
408IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_OFF
409// - Wrapper for standard libs functions. (Note that imgui_demo.cpp does _not_ use them to keep the code easy to copy)
410#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEFAULT_MATH_FUNCTIONS
411#define ImFabs(X) fabsf(X)
412#define ImSqrt(X) sqrtf(X)
413#define ImFmod(X, Y) fmodf((X), (Y))
414#define ImCos(X) cosf(X)
415#define ImSin(X) sinf(X)
416#define ImAcos(X) acosf(X)
417#define ImAtan2(Y, X) atan2f((Y), (X))
418#define ImAtof(STR) atof(STR)
419//#define ImFloorStd(X) floorf(X) // We use our own, see ImFloor() and ImFloorSigned()
420#define ImCeil(X) ceilf(X)
421static inline float ImPow(float x, float y) { return powf(x, y); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImPow with either float/double and need the precision
422static inline double ImPow(double x, double y) { return pow(x, y); }
423static inline float ImLog(float x) { return logf(x); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImLog with either float/double and need the precision
424static inline double ImLog(double x) { return log(x); }
425static inline int ImAbs(int x) { return x < 0 ? -x : x; }
426static inline float ImAbs(float x) { return fabsf(x); }
427static inline double ImAbs(double x) { return fabs(x); }
428static inline float ImSign(float x) { return (x < 0.0f) ? -1.0f : (x > 0.0f) ? 1.0f : 0.0f; } // Sign operator - returns -1, 0 or 1 based on sign of argument
429static inline double ImSign(double x) { return (x < 0.0) ? -1.0 : (x > 0.0) ? 1.0 : 0.0; }
430#ifdef IMGUI_ENABLE_SSE
431static inline float ImRsqrt(float x) { return _mm_cvtss_f32(_mm_rsqrt_ss(_mm_set_ss(x))); }
432#else
433static inline float ImRsqrt(float x) { return 1.0f / sqrtf(x); }
434#endif
435static inline double ImRsqrt(double x) { return 1.0 / sqrt(x); }
436#endif
437// - ImMin/ImMax/ImClamp/ImLerp/ImSwap are used by widgets which support variety of types: signed/unsigned int/long long float/double
438// (Exceptionally using templates here but we could also redefine them for those types)
439template<typename T> static inline T ImMin(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
440template<typename T> static inline T ImMax(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
441template<typename T> static inline T ImClamp(T v, T mn, T mx) { return (v < mn) ? mn : (v > mx) ? mx : v; }
442template<typename T> static inline T ImLerp(T a, T b, float t) { return (T)(a + (b - a) * t); }
443template<typename T> static inline void ImSwap(T& a, T& b) { T tmp = a; a = b; b = tmp; }
444template<typename T> static inline T ImAddClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b < 0 && (a < mn - b)) return mn; if (b > 0 && (a > mx - b)) return mx; return a + b; }
445template<typename T> static inline T ImSubClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b > 0 && (a < mn + b)) return mn; if (b < 0 && (a > mx + b)) return mx; return a - b; }
446// - Misc maths helpers
447static inline ImVec2 ImMin(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x < rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y < rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
448static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x >= rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y >= rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
449static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& v, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2((v.x < mn.x) ? mn.x : (v.x > mx.x) ? mx.x : v.x, (v.y < mn.y) ? mn.y : (v.y > mx.y) ? mx.y : v.y); }
450static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, float t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t); }
451static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }
452static inline ImVec4 ImLerp(const ImVec4& a, const ImVec4& b, float t) { return ImVec4(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, a.z + (b.z - a.z) * t, a.w + (b.w - a.w) * t); }
453static inline float ImSaturate(float f) { return (f < 0.0f) ? 0.0f : (f > 1.0f) ? 1.0f : f; }
454static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec2& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); }
455static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec4& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y) + (lhs.z * lhs.z) + (lhs.w * lhs.w); }
456static inline float ImInvLength(const ImVec2& lhs, float fail_value) { float d = (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); if (d > 0.0f) return ImRsqrt(d); return fail_value; }
457static inline float ImFloor(float f) { return (float)(int)(f); }
458static inline float ImFloorSigned(float f) { return (float)((f >= 0 || (float)(int)f == f) ? (int)f : (int)f - 1); } // Decent replacement for floorf()
459static inline ImVec2 ImFloor(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2((float)(int)(v.x), (float)(int)(v.y)); }
460static inline ImVec2 ImFloorSigned(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2(ImFloorSigned(v.x), ImFloorSigned(v.y)); }
461static inline int ImModPositive(int a, int b) { return (a + b) % b; }
462static inline float ImDot(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b) { return a.x * b.x + a.y * b.y; }
463static inline ImVec2 ImRotate(const ImVec2& v, float cos_a, float sin_a) { return ImVec2(v.x * cos_a - v.y * sin_a, v.x * sin_a + v.y * cos_a); }
464static inline float ImLinearSweep(float current, float target, float speed) { if (current < target) return ImMin(current + speed, target); if (current > target) return ImMax(current - speed, target); return current; }
465static inline ImVec2 ImMul(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }
466static inline bool ImIsFloatAboveGuaranteedIntegerPrecision(float f) { return f <= -16777216 || f >= 16777216; }
467IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_RESTORE

472IMGUI_API ImVec2 ImBezierCubicClosestPointCasteljau(const ImVec2& p1, const ImVec2& p2, const ImVec2& p3, const ImVec2& p4, const ImVec2& p, float tess_tol);// For auto-tessellated curves you can use tess_tol = style.CurveTessellationTol

500// Helper: ImRect (2D axis aligned bounding-box)
501// NB: we can't rely on ImVec2 math operators being available here!
502struct IMGUI_API ImRect
503{
504 ImVec2 Min; // Upper-left
505 ImVec2 Max; // Lower-right
506
507 constexpr ImRect() : Min(0.0f, 0.0f), Max(0.0f, 0.0f) {}
508 constexpr ImRect(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) : Min(min), Max(max) {}
509 constexpr ImRect(const ImVec4& v) : Min(v.x, v.y), Max(v.z, v.w) {}
510 constexpr ImRect(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) : Min(x1, y1), Max(x2, y2) {}
511
512 ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2((Min.x + Max.x) * 0.5f, (Min.y + Max.y) * 0.5f); }
513 ImVec2 GetSize() const { return ImVec2(Max.x - Min.x, Max.y - Min.y); }
514 float GetWidth() const { return Max.x - Min.x; }
515 float GetHeight() const { return Max.y - Min.y; }
516 float GetArea() const { return (Max.x - Min.x) * (Max.y - Min.y); }
517 ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; } // Top-left
518 ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x, Min.y); } // Top-right
519 ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x, Max.y); } // Bottom-left
520 ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; } // Bottom-right
521 bool Contains(const ImVec2& p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x < Max.x && p.y < Max.y; }
522 bool Contains(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
523 bool Overlaps(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.y < Max.y && r.Max.y > Min.y && r.Min.x < Max.x && r.Max.x > Min.x; }
524 void Add(const ImVec2& p) { if (Min.x > p.x) Min.x = p.x; if (Min.y > p.y) Min.y = p.y; if (Max.x < p.x) Max.x = p.x; if (Max.y < p.y) Max.y = p.y; }
525 void Add(const ImRect& r) { if (Min.x > r.Min.x) Min.x = r.Min.x; if (Min.y > r.Min.y) Min.y = r.Min.y; if (Max.x < r.Max.x) Max.x = r.Max.x; if (Max.y < r.Max.y) Max.y = r.Max.y; }
526 void Expand(const float amount) { Min.x -= amount; Min.y -= amount; Max.x += amount; Max.y += amount; }
527 void Expand(const ImVec2& amount) { Min.x -= amount.x; Min.y -= amount.y; Max.x += amount.x; Max.y += amount.y; }
528 void Translate(const ImVec2& d) { Min.x += d.x; Min.y += d.y; Max.x += d.x; Max.y += d.y; }
529 void TranslateX(float dx) { Min.x += dx; Max.x += dx; }
530 void TranslateY(float dy) { Min.y += dy; Max.y += dy; }
531 void ClipWith(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImMax(Min, r.Min); Max = ImMin(Max, r.Max); } // Simple version, may lead to an inverted rectangle, which is fine for Contains/Overlaps test but not for display.
532 void ClipWithFull(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImClamp(Min, r.Min, r.Max); Max = ImClamp(Max, r.Min, r.Max); } // Full version, ensure both points are fully clipped.
533 void Floor() { Min.x = IM_FLOOR(Min.x); Min.y = IM_FLOOR(Min.y); Max.x = IM_FLOOR(Max.x); Max.y = IM_FLOOR(Max.y); }
534 bool IsInverted() const { return Min.x > Max.x || Min.y > Max.y; }
535 ImVec4 ToVec4() const { return ImVec4(Min.x, Min.y, Max.x, Max.y); }
536};
537IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_RESTORE
538
539// Helper: ImBitArray
540inline bool ImBitArrayTestBit(const ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); return (arr[n >> 5] & mask) != 0; }
541inline void ImBitArrayClearBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] &= ~mask; }
542inline void ImBitArraySetBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] |= mask; }
543inline void ImBitArraySetBitRange(ImU32* arr, int n, int n2) // Works on range [n..n2)
544{
545 n2--;
546 while (n <= n2)
547 {
548 int a_mod = (n & 31);
549 int b_mod = (n2 > (n | 31) ? 31 : (n2 & 31)) + 1;
550 ImU32 mask = (ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << b_mod) - 1) & ~(ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << a_mod) - 1);
551 arr[n >> 5] |= mask;
552 n = (n + 32) & ~31;
553 }
554}
555
556// Helper: ImBitArray class (wrapper over ImBitArray functions)
557// Store 1-bit per value.
558template<int BITCOUNT, int OFFSET = 0>
559struct ImBitArray
560{
561 ImU32 Storage[(BITCOUNT + 31) >> 5];
562 ImBitArray() { ClearAllBits(); }
563 void ClearAllBits() { memset(Storage, 0, sizeof(Storage)); }
564 void SetAllBits() { memset(Storage, 255, sizeof(Storage)); }
565 bool TestBit(int n) const { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage, n); }
566 void SetBit(int n) { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage, n); }
567 void ClearBit(int n) { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage, n); }
568 void SetBitRange(int n, int n2) { n += OFFSET; n2 += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT && n2 > n && n2 <= BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBitRange(Storage, n, n2); } // Works on range [n..n2)
569 bool operator[](int n) const { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage, n); }
570};
571
572// Helper: ImBitVector
573// Store 1-bit per value.
574struct IMGUI_API ImBitVector
575{
576 ImVector<ImU32> Storage;
577 void Create(int sz) { Storage.resize((sz + 31) >> 5); memset(Storage.Data, 0, (size_t)Storage.Size * sizeof(Storage.Data[0])); }
578 void Clear() { Storage.clear(); }
579 bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage.Data, n); }
580 void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage.Data, n); }
581 void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage.Data, n); }
582};
583
584// Helper: ImSpan<>
585// Pointing to a span of data we don't own.
586template<typename T>
587struct ImSpan
588{
589 T* Data;
590 T* DataEnd;
591
592 // Constructors, destructor
593 inline ImSpan() { Data = DataEnd = NULL; }
594 inline ImSpan(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
595 inline ImSpan(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
596
597 inline void set(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
598 inline void set(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
599 inline int size() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data); }
600 inline int size_in_bytes() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data) * (int)sizeof(T); }
601 inline T& operator[](int i) { T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
602 inline const T& operator[](int i) const { const T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
603
604 inline T* begin() { return Data; }
605 inline const T* begin() const { return Data; }
606 inline T* end() { return DataEnd; }
607 inline const T* end() const { return DataEnd; }
608
609 // Utilities
610 inline int index_from_ptr(const T* it) const { IM_ASSERT(it >= Data && it < DataEnd); const ptrdiff_t off = it - Data; return (int)off; }
611};
612
613// Helper: ImSpanAllocator<>
614// Facilitate storing multiple chunks into a single large block (the "arena")
615// - Usage: call Reserve() N times, allocate GetArenaSizeInBytes() worth, pass it to SetArenaBasePtr(), call GetSpan() N times to retrieve the aligned ranges.
616template<int CHUNKS>
617struct ImSpanAllocator
618{
619 char* BasePtr;
620 int CurrOff;
621 int CurrIdx;
622 int Offsets[CHUNKS];
623 int Sizes[CHUNKS];
624
625 ImSpanAllocator() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
626 inline void Reserve(int n, size_t sz, int a=4) { IM_ASSERT(n == CurrIdx && n < CHUNKS); CurrOff = IM_MEMALIGN(CurrOff, a); Offsets[n] = CurrOff; Sizes[n] = (int)sz; CurrIdx++; CurrOff += (int)sz; }
627 inline int GetArenaSizeInBytes() { return CurrOff; }
628 inline void SetArenaBasePtr(void* base_ptr) { BasePtr = (char*)base_ptr; }
629 inline void* GetSpanPtrBegin(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n]); }
630 inline void* GetSpanPtrEnd(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n] + Sizes[n]); }
631 template<typename T>
632 inline void GetSpan(int n, ImSpan<T>* span) { span->set((T*)GetSpanPtrBegin(n), (T*)GetSpanPtrEnd(n)); }
633};
634
635// Helper: ImPool<>
636// Basic keyed storage for contiguous instances, slow/amortized insertion, O(1) indexable, O(Log N) queries by ID over a dense/hot buffer,
637// Honor constructor/destructor. Add/remove invalidate all pointers. Indexes have the same lifetime as the associated object.
638typedef int ImPoolIdx;
639template<typename T>
640struct ImPool
641{
642 ImVector<T> Buf; // Contiguous data
643 ImGuiStorage Map; // ID->Index
644 ImPoolIdx FreeIdx; // Next free idx to use
645 ImPoolIdx AliveCount; // Number of active/alive items (for display purpose)
646
647 ImPool() { FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
648 ~ImPool() { Clear(); }
649 T* GetByKey(ImGuiID key) { int idx = Map.GetInt(key, -1); return (idx != -1) ? &Buf[idx] : NULL; }
650 T* GetByIndex(ImPoolIdx n) { return &Buf[n]; }
651 ImPoolIdx GetIndex(const T* p) const { IM_ASSERT(p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); return (ImPoolIdx)(p - Buf.Data); }
652 T* GetOrAddByKey(ImGuiID key) { int* p_idx = Map.GetIntRef(key, -1); if (*p_idx != -1) return &Buf[*p_idx]; *p_idx = FreeIdx; return Add(); }
653 bool Contains(const T* p) const { return (p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
654 void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < Map.Data.Size; n++) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx != -1) Buf[idx].~T(); } Map.Clear(); Buf.clear(); FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
655 T* Add() { int idx = FreeIdx; if (idx == Buf.Size) { Buf.resize(Buf.Size + 1); FreeIdx++; } else { FreeIdx = *(int*)&Buf[idx]; } IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(&Buf[idx]) T(); AliveCount++; return &Buf[idx]; }
656 void Remove(ImGuiID key, const T* p) { Remove(key, GetIndex(p)); }
657 void Remove(ImGuiID key, ImPoolIdx idx) { Buf[idx].~T(); *(int*)&Buf[idx] = FreeIdx; FreeIdx = idx; Map.SetInt(key, -1); AliveCount--; }
658 void Reserve(int capacity) { Buf.reserve(capacity); Map.Data.reserve(capacity); }
659
660 // To iterate a ImPool: for (int n = 0; n < pool.GetMapSize(); n++) if (T* t = pool.TryGetMapData(n)) { ... }
661 // Can be avoided if you know .Remove() has never been called on the pool, or AliveCount == GetMapSize()
662 int GetAliveCount() const { return AliveCount; } // Number of active/alive items in the pool (for display purpose)
663 int GetBufSize() const { return Buf.Size; }
664 int GetMapSize() const { return Map.Data.Size; } // It is the map we need iterate to find valid items, since we don't have "alive" storage anywhere
665 T* TryGetMapData(ImPoolIdx n) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx == -1) return NULL; return GetByIndex(idx); }
666#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_OBSOLETE_FUNCTIONS
667 int GetSize() { return GetMapSize(); } // For ImPlot: should use GetMapSize() from (IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18304)
668#endif
669};
670
671// Helper: ImChunkStream<>
672// Build and iterate a contiguous stream of variable-sized structures.
673// This is used by Settings to store persistent data while reducing allocation count.
674// We store the chunk size first, and align the final size on 4 bytes boundaries.
675// The tedious/zealous amount of casting is to avoid -Wcast-align warnings.
676template<typename T>
677struct ImChunkStream
678{
679 ImVector<char> Buf;
680
681 void clear() { Buf.clear(); }
682 bool empty() const { return Buf.Size == 0; }
683 int size() const { return Buf.Size; }
684 T* alloc_chunk(size_t sz) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; sz = IM_MEMALIGN(HDR_SZ + sz, 4u); int off = Buf.Size; Buf.resize(off + (int)sz); ((int*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off))[0] = (int)sz; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off + (int)HDR_SZ); }
685 T* begin() { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; if (!Buf.Data) return NULL; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + HDR_SZ); }
686 T* next_chunk(T* p) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); p = (T*)(void*)((char*)(void*)p + chunk_size(p)); if (p == (T*)(void*)((char*)end() + HDR_SZ)) return (T*)0; IM_ASSERT(p < end()); return p; }
687 int chunk_size(const T* p) { return ((const int*)p)[-1]; }
688 T* end() { return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
689 int offset_from_ptr(const T* p) { IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); const ptrdiff_t off = (const char*)p - Buf.Data; return (int)off; }
690 T* ptr_from_offset(int off) { IM_ASSERT(off >= 4 && off < Buf.Size); return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off); }
691 void swap(ImChunkStream<T>& rhs) { rhs.Buf.swap(Buf); }
692
693};
694
695//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
696// [SECTION] ImDrawList support
697//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
698
699// ImDrawList: Helper function to calculate a circle's segment count given its radius and a "maximum error" value.
700// Estimation of number of circle segment based on error is derived using method described in https://stackoverflow.com/a/2244088/15194693
701// Number of segments (N) is calculated using equation:
702// N = ceil ( pi / acos(1 - error / r) ) where r > 0, error <= r
703// Our equation is significantly simpler that one in the post thanks for choosing segment that is
704// perpendicular to X axis. Follow steps in the article from this starting condition and you will
705// will get this result.
706//
707// Rendering circles with an odd number of segments, while mathematically correct will produce
708// asymmetrical results on the raster grid. Therefore we're rounding N to next even number (7->8, 8->8, 9->10 etc.)
709//
710#define IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN(_V) ((((_V) + 1) / 2) * 2)
711#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN 4
712#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX 512
713#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC(_RAD,_MAXERROR) ImClamp(IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN((int)ImCeil(IM_PI / ImAcos(1 - ImMin((_MAXERROR), (_RAD)) / (_RAD)))), IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN, IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX)
714
715// Raw equation from IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC rewritten for 'r' and 'error'.
716#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_R(_N,_MAXERROR) ((_MAXERROR) / (1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))))
717#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_ERROR(_N,_RAD) ((1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))) / (_RAD))
718
719// ImDrawList: Lookup table size for adaptive arc drawing, cover full circle.
720#ifndef IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE
721#define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE 48 // Number of samples in lookup table.
722#endif
723#define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_SAMPLE_MAX IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE // Sample index _PathArcToFastEx() for 360 angle.
724
725// Data shared between all ImDrawList instances
726// You may want to create your own instance of this if you want to use ImDrawList completely without ImGui. In that case, watch out for future changes to this structure.
727struct IMGUI_API ImDrawListSharedData
728{
729 ImVec2 TexUvWhitePixel; // UV of white pixel in the atlas
730 ImFont* Font; // Current/default font (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
731 float FontSize; // Current/default font size (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
732 float CurveTessellationTol; // Tessellation tolerance when using PathBezierCurveTo()
733 float CircleSegmentMaxError; // Number of circle segments to use per pixel of radius for AddCircle() etc
734 ImVec4 ClipRectFullscreen; // Value for PushClipRectFullscreen()
735 ImDrawListFlags InitialFlags; // Initial flags at the beginning of the frame (it is possible to alter flags on a per-drawlist basis afterwards)
736
737 // [Internal] Lookup tables
738 ImVec2 ArcFastVtx[IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE]; // Sample points on the quarter of the circle.
739 float ArcFastRadiusCutoff; // Cutoff radius after which arc drawing will fallback to slower PathArcTo()
740 ImU8 CircleSegmentCounts[64]; // Precomputed segment count for given radius before we calculate it dynamically (to avoid calculation overhead)
741 const ImVec4* TexUvLines; // UV of anti-aliased lines in the atlas
742
743 ImDrawListSharedData();
744 void SetCircleTessellationMaxError(float max_error);
745};
746
747struct ImDrawDataBuilder
748{
749 ImVector<ImDrawList*> Layers[2]; // Global layers for: regular, tooltip
750
751 void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Layers); n++) Layers[n].resize(0); }
752 void ClearFreeMemory() { for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Layers); n++) Layers[n].clear(); }
753 int GetDrawListCount() const { int count = 0; for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Layers); n++) count += Layers[n].Size; return count; }
754 IMGUI_API void FlattenIntoSingleLayer();
755};

761// Transient per-window flags, reset at the beginning of the frame. For child window, inherited from parent on first Begin().
762// This is going to be exposed in imgui.h when stabilized enough.
763enum ImGuiItemFlags_
764{
765 ImGuiItemFlags_None = 0,
766 ImGuiItemFlags_NoTabStop = 1 << 0, // false // Disable keyboard tabbing (FIXME: should merge with _NoNav)
767 ImGuiItemFlags_ButtonRepeat = 1 << 1, // false // Button() will return true multiple times based on io.KeyRepeatDelay and io.KeyRepeatRate settings.
768 ImGuiItemFlags_Disabled = 1 << 2, // false // Disable interactions but doesn't affect visuals. See BeginDisabled()/EndDisabled(). See github.com/ocornut/imgui/issues/211
769 ImGuiItemFlags_NoNav = 1 << 3, // false // Disable keyboard/gamepad directional navigation (FIXME: should merge with _NoTabStop)
770 ImGuiItemFlags_NoNavDefaultFocus = 1 << 4, // false // Disable item being a candidate for default focus (e.g. used by title bar items)
771 ImGuiItemFlags_SelectableDontClosePopup = 1 << 5, // false // Disable MenuItem/Selectable() automatically closing their popup window
772 ImGuiItemFlags_MixedValue = 1 << 6, // false // [BETA] Represent a mixed/indeterminate value, generally multi-selection where values differ. Currently only supported by Checkbox() (later should support all sorts of widgets)
773 ImGuiItemFlags_ReadOnly = 1 << 7, // false // [ALPHA] Allow hovering interactions but underlying value is not changed.
774 ImGuiItemFlags_Inputable = 1 << 8 // false // [WIP] Auto-activate input mode when tab focused. Currently only used and supported by a few items before it becomes a generic feature.
775};

1009// Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
1010// For a given item ID, access with ImGui::GetInputTextState()
1011struct IMGUI_API ImGuiInputTextState
1012{
1013 ImGuiID ID; // widget id owning the text state
1014 int CurLenW, CurLenA; // we need to maintain our buffer length in both UTF-8 and wchar format. UTF-8 length is valid even if TextA is not.
1015 ImVector<ImWchar> TextW; // edit buffer, we need to persist but can't guarantee the persistence of the user-provided buffer. so we copy into own buffer.
1016 ImVector<char> TextA; // temporary UTF8 buffer for callbacks and other operations. this is not updated in every code-path! size=capacity.
1017 ImVector<char> InitialTextA; // backup of end-user buffer at the time of focus (in UTF-8, unaltered)
1018 bool TextAIsValid; // temporary UTF8 buffer is not initially valid before we make the widget active (until then we pull the data from user argument)
1019 int BufCapacityA; // end-user buffer capacity
1020 float ScrollX; // horizontal scrolling/offset
1021 ImStb::STB_TexteditState Stb; // state for stb_textedit.h
1022 float CursorAnim; // timer for cursor blink, reset on every user action so the cursor reappears immediately
1023 bool CursorFollow; // set when we want scrolling to follow the current cursor position (not always!)
1024 bool SelectedAllMouseLock; // after a double-click to select all, we ignore further mouse drags to update selection
1025 bool Edited; // edited this frame
1026 ImGuiInputTextFlags Flags; // copy of InputText() flags
1027
1028 ImGuiInputTextState() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
1029 void ClearText() { CurLenW = CurLenA = 0; TextW[0] = 0; TextA[0] = 0; CursorClamp(); }
1030 void ClearFreeMemory() { TextW.clear(); TextA.clear(); InitialTextA.clear(); }
1031 int GetUndoAvailCount() const { return Stb.undostate.undo_point; }
1032 int GetRedoAvailCount() const { return STB_TEXTEDIT_UNDOSTATECOUNT - Stb.undostate.redo_point; }
1033 void OnKeyPressed(int key); // Cannot be inline because we call in code in stb_textedit.h implementation
1034
1035 // Cursor & Selection
1036 void CursorAnimReset() { CursorAnim = -0.30f; } // After a user-input the cursor stays on for a while without blinking
1037 void CursorClamp() { Stb.cursor = ImMin(Stb.cursor, CurLenW); Stb.select_start = ImMin(Stb.select_start, CurLenW); Stb.select_end = ImMin(Stb.select_end, CurLenW); }
1038 bool HasSelection() const { return Stb.select_start != Stb.select_end; }
1039 void ClearSelection() { Stb.select_start = Stb.select_end = Stb.cursor; }
1040 int GetCursorPos() const { return Stb.cursor; }
1041 int GetSelectionStart() const { return Stb.select_start; }
1042 int GetSelectionEnd() const { return Stb.select_end; }
1043 void SelectAll() { Stb.select_start = 0; Stb.cursor = Stb.select_end = CurLenW; Stb.has_preferred_x = 0; }
1044};

1300 ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleEdgeY = 1 << 1, // If item is not visible: scroll as little as possible on Y axis to bring item back into view [default for Y axis for windows that are already visible]
1301 ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleCenterX = 1 << 2, // If item is not visible: scroll to make the item centered on X axis [rarely used]
1302 ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleCenterY = 1 << 3, // If item is not visible: scroll to make the item centered on Y axis
1303 ImGuiScrollFlags_AlwaysCenterX = 1 << 4, // Always center the result item on X axis [rarely used]
1304 ImGuiScrollFlags_AlwaysCenterY = 1 << 5, // Always center the result item on Y axis [default for Y axis for appearing window)
1305 ImGuiScrollFlags_NoScrollParent = 1 << 6, // Disable forwarding scrolling to parent window if required to keep item/rect visible (only scroll window the function was applied to).
1306 ImGuiScrollFlags_MaskX_ = ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleEdgeX | ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleCenterX | ImGuiScrollFlags_AlwaysCenterX,

1438// Extend ImGuiDockNodeFlags_
1439enum ImGuiDockNodeFlagsPrivate_
1440{
1441 // [Internal]
1442 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace = 1 << 10, // Local, Saved // A dockspace is a node that occupy space within an existing user window. Otherwise the node is floating and create its own window.
1443 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode = 1 << 11, // Local, Saved // The central node has 2 main properties: stay visible when empty, only use "remaining" spaces from its neighbor.
1444 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar = 1 << 12, // Local, Saved // Tab bar is completely unavailable. No triangle in the corner to enable it back.
1445 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar = 1 << 13, // Local, Saved // Tab bar is hidden, with a triangle in the corner to show it again (NB: actual tab-bar instance may be destroyed as this is only used for single-window tab bar)
1446 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoWindowMenuButton = 1 << 14, // Local, Saved // Disable window/docking menu (that one that appears instead of the collapse button)
1447 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoCloseButton = 1 << 15, // Local, Saved //
1448 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDocking = 1 << 16, // Local, Saved // Disable any form of docking in this dockspace or individual node. (On a whole dockspace, this pretty much defeat the purpose of using a dockspace at all). Note: when turned on, existing docked nodes will be preserved.
1449 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingSplitMe = 1 << 17, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent another window/node from splitting this node.
1450 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingSplitOther = 1 << 18, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent this node from splitting another window/node.
1451 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverMe = 1 << 19, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent another window/node to be docked over this node.
1452 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverOther = 1 << 20, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent this node to be docked over another window or non-empty node.
1453 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverEmpty = 1 << 21, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent this node to be docked over an empty node (e.g. DockSpace with no other windows)
1454 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeX = 1 << 22, // [EXPERIMENTAL]
1455 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeY = 1 << 23, // [EXPERIMENTAL]
1456 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_SharedFlagsInheritMask_ = ~0,
1457 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeFlagsMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResize | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeX | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeY,
1458 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_LocalFlagsMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoSplit | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeFlagsMask_ | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_AutoHideTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoWindowMenuButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoCloseButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDocking,
1459 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_LocalFlagsTransferMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_LocalFlagsMask_ & ~ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace, // When splitting those flags are moved to the inheriting child, never duplicated
1460 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_SavedFlagsMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeFlagsMask_ | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoWindowMenuButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoCloseButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDocking
1461};

1479// sizeof() 156~192
1480struct IMGUI_API ImGuiDockNode
1481{
1482 ImGuiID ID;
1483 ImGuiDockNodeFlags SharedFlags; // (Write) Flags shared by all nodes of a same dockspace hierarchy (inherited from the root node)
1484 ImGuiDockNodeFlags LocalFlags; // (Write) Flags specific to this node
1485 ImGuiDockNodeFlags LocalFlagsInWindows; // (Write) Flags specific to this node, applied from windows
1486 ImGuiDockNodeFlags MergedFlags; // (Read) Effective flags (== SharedFlags | LocalFlagsInNode | LocalFlagsInWindows)
1487 ImGuiDockNodeState State;
1488 ImGuiDockNode* ParentNode;
1489 ImGuiDockNode* ChildNodes[2]; // [Split node only] Child nodes (left/right or top/bottom). Consider switching to an array.
1490 ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> Windows; // Note: unordered list! Iterate TabBar->Tabs for user-order.
1491 ImGuiTabBar* TabBar;
1492 ImVec2 Pos; // Current position
1493 ImVec2 Size; // Current size
1494 ImVec2 SizeRef; // [Split node only] Last explicitly written-to size (overridden when using a splitter affecting the node), used to calculate Size.
1495 ImGuiAxis SplitAxis; // [Split node only] Split axis (X or Y)
1496 ImGuiWindowClass WindowClass; // [Root node only]
1497 ImU32 LastBgColor;
1498
1499 ImGuiWindow* HostWindow;
1500 ImGuiWindow* VisibleWindow; // Generally point to window which is ID is == SelectedTabID, but when CTRL+Tabbing this can be a different window.
1501 ImGuiDockNode* CentralNode; // [Root node only] Pointer to central node.
1502 ImGuiDockNode* OnlyNodeWithWindows; // [Root node only] Set when there is a single visible node within the hierarchy.
1503 int CountNodeWithWindows; // [Root node only]
1504 int LastFrameAlive; // Last frame number the node was updated or kept alive explicitly with DockSpace() + ImGuiDockNodeFlags_KeepAliveOnly
1505 int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number the node was updated.
1506 int LastFrameFocused; // Last frame number the node was focused.
1507 ImGuiID LastFocusedNodeId; // [Root node only] Which of our child docking node (any ancestor in the hierarchy) was last focused.
1508 ImGuiID SelectedTabId; // [Leaf node only] Which of our tab/window is selected.
1509 ImGuiID WantCloseTabId; // [Leaf node only] Set when closing a specific tab/window.
1510 ImGuiDataAuthority AuthorityForPos :3;
1511 ImGuiDataAuthority AuthorityForSize :3;
1512 ImGuiDataAuthority AuthorityForViewport :3;
1513 bool IsVisible :1; // Set to false when the node is hidden (usually disabled as it has no active window)
1514 bool IsFocused :1;
1515 bool IsBgDrawnThisFrame :1;
1516 bool HasCloseButton :1; // Provide space for a close button (if any of the docked window has one). Note that button may be hidden on window without one.
1517 bool HasWindowMenuButton :1;
1518 bool HasCentralNodeChild :1;
1519 bool WantCloseAll :1; // Set when closing all tabs at once.
1520 bool WantLockSizeOnce :1;
1521 bool WantMouseMove :1; // After a node extraction we need to transition toward moving the newly created host window
1522 bool WantHiddenTabBarUpdate :1;
1523 bool WantHiddenTabBarToggle :1;
1524
1525 ImGuiDockNode(ImGuiID id);
1526 ~ImGuiDockNode();
1527 bool IsRootNode() const { return ParentNode == NULL; }
1528 bool IsDockSpace() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace) != 0; }
1529 bool IsFloatingNode() const { return ParentNode == NULL && (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace) == 0; }
1530 bool IsCentralNode() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode) != 0; }
1531 bool IsHiddenTabBar() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar) != 0; } // Hidden tab bar can be shown back by clicking the small triangle
1532 bool IsNoTabBar() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar) != 0; } // Never show a tab bar
1533 bool IsSplitNode() const { return ChildNodes[0] != NULL; }
1534 bool IsLeafNode() const { return ChildNodes[0] == NULL; }
1535 bool IsEmpty() const { return ChildNodes[0] == NULL && Windows.Size == 0; }
1536 ImRect Rect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1537
1538 void SetLocalFlags(ImGuiDockNodeFlags flags) { LocalFlags = flags; UpdateMergedFlags(); }
1539 void UpdateMergedFlags() { MergedFlags = SharedFlags | LocalFlags | LocalFlagsInWindows; }
1540};

1573//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1574// [SECTION] Viewport support
1575//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1576
1577// ImGuiViewport Private/Internals fields (cardinal sin: we are using inheritance!)
1578// Every instance of ImGuiViewport is in fact a ImGuiViewportP.
1579struct ImGuiViewportP : public ImGuiViewport
1580{
1581 int Idx;
1582 int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number this viewport was activated by a window
1583 int LastFrontMostStampCount;// Last stamp number from when a window hosted by this viewport was made front-most (by comparing this value between two viewport we have an implicit viewport z-order
1584 ImGuiID LastNameHash;
1585 ImVec2 LastPos;
1586 float Alpha; // Window opacity (when dragging dockable windows/viewports we make them transparent)
1587 float LastAlpha;
1588 short PlatformMonitor;
1589 bool PlatformWindowCreated;
1590 ImGuiWindow* Window; // Set when the viewport is owned by a window (and ImGuiViewportFlags_CanHostOtherWindows is NOT set)
1591 int DrawListsLastFrame[2]; // Last frame number the background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists were used
1592 ImDrawList* DrawLists[2]; // Convenience background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists. We use them to draw software mouser cursor when io.MouseDrawCursor is set and to draw most debug overlays.
1593 ImDrawData DrawDataP;
1594 ImDrawDataBuilder DrawDataBuilder;
1595 ImVec2 LastPlatformPos;
1596 ImVec2 LastPlatformSize;
1597 ImVec2 LastRendererSize;
1598 ImVec2 WorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset from Pos to top-left corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,+main_menu_bar_height). Work Area is Full Area but without menu-bars/status-bars (so WorkArea always fit inside Pos/Size!)
1599 ImVec2 WorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset from Pos+Size to bottom-right corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,-status_bar_height).
1600 ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally >= 0.0f.
1601 ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally <= 0.0f.
1602
1603 ImGuiViewportP() { Idx = -1; LastFrameActive = DrawListsLastFrame[0] = DrawListsLastFrame[1] = LastFrontMostStampCount = -1; LastNameHash = 0; Alpha = LastAlpha = 1.0f; PlatformMonitor = -1; PlatformWindowCreated = false; Window = NULL; DrawLists[0] = DrawLists[1] = NULL; LastPlatformPos = LastPlatformSize = LastRendererSize = ImVec2(FLT_MAX, FLT_MAX); }
1604 ~ImGuiViewportP() { if (DrawLists[0]) IM_DELETE(DrawLists[0]); if (DrawLists[1]) IM_DELETE(DrawLists[1]); }
1605 void ClearRequestFlags() { PlatformRequestClose = PlatformRequestMove = PlatformRequestResize = false; }
1606
1607 // Calculate work rect pos/size given a set of offset (we have 1 pair of offset for rect locked from last frame data, and 1 pair for currently building rect)
1608 ImVec2 CalcWorkRectPos(const ImVec2& off_min) const { return ImVec2(Pos.x + off_min.x, Pos.y + off_min.y); }
1609 ImVec2 CalcWorkRectSize(const ImVec2& off_min, const ImVec2& off_max) const { return ImVec2(ImMax(0.0f, Size.x - off_min.x + off_max.x), ImMax(0.0f, Size.y - off_min.y + off_max.y)); }
1610 void UpdateWorkRect() { WorkPos = CalcWorkRectPos(WorkOffsetMin); WorkSize = CalcWorkRectSize(WorkOffsetMin, WorkOffsetMax); } // Update public fields
1611
1612 // Helpers to retrieve ImRect (we don't need to store BuildWorkRect as every access tend to change it, hence the code asymmetry)
1613 ImRect GetMainRect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1614 ImRect GetWorkRect() const { return ImRect(WorkPos.x, WorkPos.y, WorkPos.x + WorkSize.x, WorkPos.y + WorkSize.y); }
1615 ImRect GetBuildWorkRect() const { ImVec2 pos = CalcWorkRectPos(BuildWorkOffsetMin); ImVec2 size = CalcWorkRectSize(BuildWorkOffsetMin, BuildWorkOffsetMax); return ImRect(pos.x, pos.y, pos.x + size.x, pos.y + size.y); }
1616};

1619// [SECTION] Settings support
1620//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1621
1622// Windows data saved in imgui.ini file
1623// Because we never destroy or rename ImGuiWindowSettings, we can store the names in a separate buffer easily.
1624// (this is designed to be stored in a ImChunkStream buffer, with the variable-length Name following our structure)
1625struct ImGuiWindowSettings
1626{
1627 ImGuiID ID;
1628 ImVec2ih Pos; // NB: Settings position are stored RELATIVE to the viewport! Whereas runtime ones are absolute positions.
1629 ImVec2ih Size;
1630 ImVec2ih ViewportPos;
1631 ImGuiID ViewportId;
1632 ImGuiID DockId; // ID of last known DockNode (even if the DockNode is invisible because it has only 1 active window), or 0 if none.
1633 ImGuiID ClassId; // ID of window class if specified
1634 short DockOrder; // Order of the last time the window was visible within its DockNode. This is used to reorder windows that are reappearing on the same frame. Same value between windows that were active and windows that were none are possible.
1635 bool Collapsed;
1636 bool WantApply; // Set when loaded from .ini data (to enable merging/loading .ini data into an already running context)
1637
1638 ImGuiWindowSettings() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); DockOrder = -1; }
1639 char* GetName() { return (char*)(this + 1); }
1640};
1641
1642struct ImGuiSettingsHandler
1643{
1644 const char* TypeName; // Short description stored in .ini file. Disallowed characters: '[' ']'
1645 ImGuiID TypeHash; // == ImHashStr(TypeName)
1646 void (*ClearAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Clear all settings data
1647 void (*ReadInitFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Read: Called before reading (in registration order)
1648 void* (*ReadOpenFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, const char* name); // Read: Called when entering into a new ini entry e.g. "[Window][Name]"
1649 void (*ReadLineFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, void* entry, const char* line); // Read: Called for every line of text within an ini entry
1650 void (*ApplyAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Read: Called after reading (in registration order)
1651 void (*WriteAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, ImGuiTextBuffer* out_buf); // Write: Output every entries into 'out_buf'
1652 void* UserData;
1653
1654 ImGuiSettingsHandler() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
1655};

2169// Transient per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the DC variable name in ImGuiWindow.

2171// (This doesn't need a constructor because we zero-clear it as part of ImGuiWindow and all frame-temporary data are setup on Begin)
2172struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindowTempData
2173{
2174 // Layout

2185 ImVec1 ColumnsOffset; // Offset to the current column (if ColumnsCurrent > 0). FIXME: This and the above should be a stack to allow use cases like Tree->Column->Tree. Need revamp columns API.
2186 ImVec1 GroupOffset;

2200 ImGuiMenuColumns MenuColumns; // Simplified columns storage for menu items measurement

2218// Storage for one window

2254 bool WantCollapseToggle;
2255 bool SkipItems; // Set when items can safely be all clipped (e.g. window not visible or collapsed)
2256 bool Appearing; // Set during the frame where the window is appearing (or re-appearing)
2257 bool Hidden; // Do not display (== HiddenFrames*** > 0)
2258 bool IsFallbackWindow; // Set on the "Debug##Default" window.
2259 bool IsExplicitChild; // Set when passed _ChildWindow, left to false by BeginDocked()
2260 bool HasCloseButton; // Set when the window has a close button (p_open != NULL)
2261 signed char ResizeBorderHeld; // Current border being held for resize (-1: none, otherwise 0-3)
2262 short BeginCount; // Number of Begin() during the current frame (generally 0 or 1, 1+ if appending via multiple Begin/End pairs)
2263 short BeginOrderWithinParent; // Begin() order within immediate parent window, if we are a child window. Otherwise 0.
2264 short BeginOrderWithinContext; // Begin() order within entire imgui context. This is mostly used for debugging submission order related issues.
2265 short FocusOrder; // Order within WindowsFocusOrder[], altered when windows are focused.
2266 ImGuiID PopupId; // ID in the popup stack when this window is used as a popup/menu (because we use generic Name/ID for recycling)
2267 ImS8 AutoFitFramesX, AutoFitFramesY;
2268 ImS8 AutoFitChildAxises;
2269 bool AutoFitOnlyGrows;
2270 ImGuiDir AutoPosLastDirection;
2271 ImS8 HiddenFramesCanSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames
2272 ImS8 HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames while allowing items to be submitted so we can measure their size
2273 ImS8 HiddenFramesForRenderOnly; // Hide the window until frame N at Render() time only
2274 ImS8 DisableInputsFrames; // Disable window interactions for N frames
2275 ImGuiCond SetWindowPosAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowPos() use.
2276 ImGuiCond SetWindowSizeAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowSize() use.
2277 ImGuiCond SetWindowCollapsedAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowCollapsed() use.

2280 ImVec2 SetWindowPosPivot; // store window pivot for positioning. ImVec2(0, 0) when positioning from top-left corner; ImVec2(0.5f, 0.5f) for centering; ImVec2(1, 1) for bottom right.
2281

2283 ImGuiWindowTempData DC; // Temporary per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the "DC" variable name.
2284

2350 // We don't use g.FontSize because the window may be != g.CurrentWidow.
2351 ImRect Rect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
2352 float CalcFontSize() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; float scale = g.FontBaseSize * FontWindowScale * FontDpiScale; if (ParentWindow) scale *= ParentWindow->FontWindowScale; return scale; }
2353 float TitleBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) ? 0.0f : CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f; }

2356 ImRect MenuBarRect() const { float y1 = Pos.y + TitleBarHeight(); return ImRect(Pos.x, y1, Pos.x + SizeFull.x, y1 + MenuBarHeight()); }

2446//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2447// [SECTION] Table support
2448//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2449
2450#define IM_COL32_DISABLE IM_COL32(0,0,0,1) // Special sentinel code which cannot be used as a regular color.
2451#define IMGUI_TABLE_MAX_COLUMNS 64 // sizeof(ImU64) * 8. This is solely because we frequently encode columns set in a ImU64.
2452#define IMGUI_TABLE_MAX_DRAW_CHANNELS (4 + 64 * 2) // See TableSetupDrawChannels()
2453
2454// Our current column maximum is 64 but we may raise that in the future.
2455typedef ImS8 ImGuiTableColumnIdx;
2456typedef ImU8 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx;
2457
2458// [Internal] sizeof() ~ 104
2459// We use the terminology "Enabled" to refer to a column that is not Hidden by user/api.
2460// We use the terminology "Clipped" to refer to a column that is out of sight because of scrolling/clipping.
2461// This is in contrast with some user-facing api such as IsItemVisible() / IsRectVisible() which use "Visible" to mean "not clipped".
2462struct ImGuiTableColumn
2463{
2464 ImGuiTableColumnFlags Flags; // Flags after some patching (not directly same as provided by user). See ImGuiTableColumnFlags_
2465 float WidthGiven; // Final/actual width visible == (MaxX - MinX), locked in TableUpdateLayout(). May be > WidthRequest to honor minimum width, may be < WidthRequest to honor shrinking columns down in tight space.
2466 float MinX; // Absolute positions
2467 float MaxX;
2468 float WidthRequest; // Master width absolute value when !(Flags & _WidthStretch). When Stretch this is derived every frame from StretchWeight in TableUpdateLayout()
2469 float WidthAuto; // Automatic width
2470 float StretchWeight; // Master width weight when (Flags & _WidthStretch). Often around ~1.0f initially.
2471 float InitStretchWeightOrWidth; // Value passed to TableSetupColumn(). For Width it is a content width (_without padding_).
2472 ImRect ClipRect; // Clipping rectangle for the column
2473 ImGuiID UserID; // Optional, value passed to TableSetupColumn()
2474 float WorkMinX; // Contents region min ~(MinX + CellPaddingX + CellSpacingX1) == cursor start position when entering column
2475 float WorkMaxX; // Contents region max ~(MaxX - CellPaddingX - CellSpacingX2)
2476 float ItemWidth; // Current item width for the column, preserved across rows
2477 float ContentMaxXFrozen; // Contents maximum position for frozen rows (apart from headers), from which we can infer content width.
2478 float ContentMaxXUnfrozen;
2479 float ContentMaxXHeadersUsed; // Contents maximum position for headers rows (regardless of freezing). TableHeader() automatically softclip itself + report ideal desired size, to avoid creating extraneous draw calls
2480 float ContentMaxXHeadersIdeal;
2481 ImS16 NameOffset; // Offset into parent ColumnsNames[]
2482 ImGuiTableColumnIdx DisplayOrder; // Index within Table's IndexToDisplayOrder[] (column may be reordered by users)
2483 ImGuiTableColumnIdx IndexWithinEnabledSet; // Index within enabled/visible set (<= IndexToDisplayOrder)
2484 ImGuiTableColumnIdx PrevEnabledColumn; // Index of prev enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if first enabled/visible column
2485 ImGuiTableColumnIdx NextEnabledColumn; // Index of next enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if last enabled/visible column
2486 ImGuiTableColumnIdx SortOrder; // Index of this column within sort specs, -1 if not sorting on this column, 0 for single-sort, may be >0 on multi-sort
2487 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelCurrent; // Index within DrawSplitter.Channels[]
2488 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelFrozen; // Draw channels for frozen rows (often headers)
2489 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelUnfrozen; // Draw channels for unfrozen rows
2490 bool IsEnabled; // IsUserEnabled && (Flags & ImGuiTableColumnFlags_Disabled) == 0
2491 bool IsUserEnabled; // Is the column not marked Hidden by the user? (unrelated to being off view, e.g. clipped by scrolling).
2492 bool IsUserEnabledNextFrame;
2493 bool IsVisibleX; // Is actually in view (e.g. overlapping the host window clipping rectangle, not scrolled).
2494 bool IsVisibleY;
2495 bool IsRequestOutput; // Return value for TableSetColumnIndex() / TableNextColumn(): whether we request user to output contents or not.
2496 bool IsSkipItems; // Do we want item submissions to this column to be completely ignored (no layout will happen).
2497 bool IsPreserveWidthAuto;
2498 ImS8 NavLayerCurrent; // ImGuiNavLayer in 1 byte
2499 ImU8 AutoFitQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to request auto-fit
2500 ImU8 CannotSkipItemsQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to disable Clipped/SkipItem
2501 ImU8 SortDirection : 2; // ImGuiSortDirection_Ascending or ImGuiSortDirection_Descending
2502 ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailCount : 2; // Number of available sort directions (0 to 3)
2503 ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailMask : 4; // Mask of available sort directions (1-bit each)
2504 ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailList; // Ordered of available sort directions (2-bits each)
2505
2506 ImGuiTableColumn()
2507 {
2508 memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this));
2509 StretchWeight = WidthRequest = -1.0f;
2510 NameOffset = -1;
2511 DisplayOrder = IndexWithinEnabledSet = -1;
2512 PrevEnabledColumn = NextEnabledColumn = -1;
2513 SortOrder = -1;
2514 SortDirection = ImGuiSortDirection_None;
2515 DrawChannelCurrent = DrawChannelFrozen = DrawChannelUnfrozen = (ImU8)-1;
2516 }
2517};

2536// FIXME-TABLE: more transient data could be stored in a per-stacked table structure: DrawSplitter, SortSpecs, incoming RowData
2537struct IMGUI_API ImGuiTable
2538{
2539 ImGuiID ID;
2540 ImGuiTableFlags Flags;
2541 void* RawData; // Single allocation to hold Columns[], DisplayOrderToIndex[] and RowCellData[]
2542 ImGuiTableTempData* TempData; // Transient data while table is active. Point within g.CurrentTableStack[]
2543 ImSpan<ImGuiTableColumn> Columns; // Point within RawData[]
2544 ImSpan<ImGuiTableColumnIdx> DisplayOrderToIndex; // Point within RawData[]. Store display order of columns (when not reordered, the values are 0...Count-1)
2545 ImSpan<ImGuiTableCellData> RowCellData; // Point within RawData[]. Store cells background requests for current row.
2546 ImU64 EnabledMaskByDisplayOrder; // Column DisplayOrder -> IsEnabled map
2547 ImU64 EnabledMaskByIndex; // Column Index -> IsEnabled map (== not hidden by user/api) in a format adequate for iterating column without touching cold data
2548 ImU64 VisibleMaskByIndex; // Column Index -> IsVisibleX|IsVisibleY map (== not hidden by user/api && not hidden by scrolling/cliprect)
2549 ImU64 RequestOutputMaskByIndex; // Column Index -> IsVisible || AutoFit (== expect user to submit items)
2550 ImGuiTableFlags SettingsLoadedFlags; // Which data were loaded from the .ini file (e.g. when order is not altered we won't save order)
2551 int SettingsOffset; // Offset in g.SettingsTables
2552 int LastFrameActive;
2553 int ColumnsCount; // Number of columns declared in BeginTable()
2554 int CurrentRow;
2555 int CurrentColumn;
2556 ImS16 InstanceCurrent; // Count of BeginTable() calls with same ID in the same frame (generally 0). This is a little bit similar to BeginCount for a window, but multiple table with same ID look are multiple tables, they are just synched.
2557 ImS16 InstanceInteracted; // Mark which instance (generally 0) of the same ID is being interacted with
2558 float RowPosY1;
2559 float RowPosY2;
2560 float RowMinHeight; // Height submitted to TableNextRow()
2561 float RowTextBaseline;
2562 float RowIndentOffsetX;
2563 ImGuiTableRowFlags RowFlags : 16; // Current row flags, see ImGuiTableRowFlags_
2564 ImGuiTableRowFlags LastRowFlags : 16;
2565 int RowBgColorCounter; // Counter for alternating background colors (can be fast-forwarded by e.g clipper), not same as CurrentRow because header rows typically don't increase this.
2566 ImU32 RowBgColor[2]; // Background color override for current row.
2567 ImU32 BorderColorStrong;
2568 ImU32 BorderColorLight;
2569 float BorderX1;
2570 float BorderX2;
2571 float HostIndentX;
2572 float MinColumnWidth;
2573 float OuterPaddingX;
2574 float CellPaddingX; // Padding from each borders
2575 float CellPaddingY;
2576 float CellSpacingX1; // Spacing between non-bordered cells
2577 float CellSpacingX2;
2578 float InnerWidth; // User value passed to BeginTable(), see comments at the top of BeginTable() for details.
2579 float ColumnsGivenWidth; // Sum of current column width
2580 float ColumnsAutoFitWidth; // Sum of ideal column width in order nothing to be clipped, used for auto-fitting and content width submission in outer window
2581 float ResizedColumnNextWidth;
2582 float ResizeLockMinContentsX2; // Lock minimum contents width while resizing down in order to not create feedback loops. But we allow growing the table.
2583 float RefScale; // Reference scale to be able to rescale columns on font/dpi changes.
2584 ImRect OuterRect; // Note: for non-scrolling table, OuterRect.Max.y is often FLT_MAX until EndTable(), unless a height has been specified in BeginTable().
2585 ImRect InnerRect; // InnerRect but without decoration. As with OuterRect, for non-scrolling tables, InnerRect.Max.y is
2586 ImRect WorkRect;
2587 ImRect InnerClipRect;
2588 ImRect BgClipRect; // We use this to cpu-clip cell background color fill, evolve during the frame as we cross frozen rows boundaries
2589 ImRect Bg0ClipRectForDrawCmd; // Actual ImDrawCmd clip rect for BG0/1 channel. This tends to be == OuterWindow->ClipRect at BeginTable() because output in BG0/BG1 is cpu-clipped
2590 ImRect Bg2ClipRectForDrawCmd; // Actual ImDrawCmd clip rect for BG2 channel. This tends to be a correct, tight-fit, because output to BG2 are done by widgets relying on regular ClipRect.
2591 ImRect HostClipRect; // This is used to check if we can eventually merge our columns draw calls into the current draw call of the current window.
2592 ImRect HostBackupInnerClipRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->ClipRect during PushTableBackground()/PopTableBackground()
2593 ImGuiWindow* OuterWindow; // Parent window for the table
2594 ImGuiWindow* InnerWindow; // Window holding the table data (== OuterWindow or a child window)
2595 ImGuiTextBuffer ColumnsNames; // Contiguous buffer holding columns names
2596 ImDrawListSplitter* DrawSplitter; // Shortcut to TempData->DrawSplitter while in table. Isolate draw commands per columns to avoid switching clip rect constantly
2597 ImGuiTableInstanceData InstanceDataFirst;
2598 ImVector<ImGuiTableInstanceData> InstanceDataExtra; // FIXME-OPT: Using a small-vector pattern would be good.
2599 ImGuiTableColumnSortSpecs SortSpecsSingle;
2600 ImVector<ImGuiTableColumnSortSpecs> SortSpecsMulti; // FIXME-OPT: Using a small-vector pattern would be good.
2601 ImGuiTableSortSpecs SortSpecs; // Public facing sorts specs, this is what we return in TableGetSortSpecs()
2602 ImGuiTableColumnIdx SortSpecsCount;
2603 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ColumnsEnabledCount; // Number of enabled columns (<= ColumnsCount)
2604 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ColumnsEnabledFixedCount; // Number of enabled columns (<= ColumnsCount)
2605 ImGuiTableColumnIdx DeclColumnsCount; // Count calls to TableSetupColumn()
2606 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBody; // Index of column whose visible region is being hovered. Important: == ColumnsCount when hovering empty region after the right-most column!
2607 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBorder; // Index of column whose right-border is being hovered (for resizing).
2608 ImGuiTableColumnIdx AutoFitSingleColumn; // Index of single column requesting auto-fit.
2609 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ResizedColumn; // Index of column being resized. Reset when InstanceCurrent==0.
2610 ImGuiTableColumnIdx LastResizedColumn; // Index of column being resized from previous frame.
2611 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HeldHeaderColumn; // Index of column header being held.
2612 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ReorderColumn; // Index of column being reordered. (not cleared)
2613 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ReorderColumnDir; // -1 or +1
2614 ImGuiTableColumnIdx LeftMostEnabledColumn; // Index of left-most non-hidden column.
2615 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RightMostEnabledColumn; // Index of right-most non-hidden column.
2616 ImGuiTableColumnIdx LeftMostStretchedColumn; // Index of left-most stretched column.
2617 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RightMostStretchedColumn; // Index of right-most stretched column.
2618 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ContextPopupColumn; // Column right-clicked on, of -1 if opening context menu from a neutral/empty spot
2619 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeRowsRequest; // Requested frozen rows count
2620 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeRowsCount; // Actual frozen row count (== FreezeRowsRequest, or == 0 when no scrolling offset)
2621 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeColumnsRequest; // Requested frozen columns count
2622 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeColumnsCount; // Actual frozen columns count (== FreezeColumnsRequest, or == 0 when no scrolling offset)
2623 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RowCellDataCurrent; // Index of current RowCellData[] entry in current row
2624 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DummyDrawChannel; // Redirect non-visible columns here.
2625 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx Bg2DrawChannelCurrent; // For Selectable() and other widgets drawing across columns after the freezing line. Index within DrawSplitter.Channels[]
2626 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx Bg2DrawChannelUnfrozen;
2627 bool IsLayoutLocked; // Set by TableUpdateLayout() which is called when beginning the first row.
2628 bool IsInsideRow; // Set when inside TableBeginRow()/TableEndRow().
2629 bool IsInitializing;
2630 bool IsSortSpecsDirty;
2631 bool IsUsingHeaders; // Set when the first row had the ImGuiTableRowFlags_Headers flag.
2632 bool IsContextPopupOpen; // Set when default context menu is open (also see: ContextPopupColumn, InstanceInteracted).
2633 bool IsSettingsRequestLoad;
2634 bool IsSettingsDirty; // Set when table settings have changed and needs to be reported into ImGuiTableSetttings data.
2635 bool IsDefaultDisplayOrder; // Set when display order is unchanged from default (DisplayOrder contains 0...Count-1)
2636 bool IsResetAllRequest;
2637 bool IsResetDisplayOrderRequest;
2638 bool IsUnfrozenRows; // Set when we got past the frozen row.
2639 bool IsDefaultSizingPolicy; // Set if user didn't explicitly set a sizing policy in BeginTable()
2640 bool MemoryCompacted;
2641 bool HostSkipItems; // Backup of InnerWindow->SkipItem at the end of BeginTable(), because we will overwrite InnerWindow->SkipItem on a per-column basis
2642
2643 ImGuiTable() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); LastFrameActive = -1; }
2644 ~ImGuiTable() { IM_FREE(RawData); }
2645};

2647// Transient data that are only needed between BeginTable() and EndTable(), those buffers are shared (1 per level of stacked table).
2648// - Accessing those requires chasing an extra pointer so for very frequently used data we leave them in the main table structure.
2649// - We also leave out of this structure data that tend to be particularly useful for debugging/metrics.
2650struct IMGUI_API ImGuiTableTempData
2651{
2652 int TableIndex; // Index in g.Tables.Buf[] pool
2653 float LastTimeActive; // Last timestamp this structure was used
2654
2655 ImVec2 UserOuterSize; // outer_size.x passed to BeginTable()
2656 ImDrawListSplitter DrawSplitter;
2657
2658 ImRect HostBackupWorkRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->WorkRect at the end of BeginTable()
2659 ImRect HostBackupParentWorkRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->ParentWorkRect at the end of BeginTable()
2660 ImVec2 HostBackupPrevLineSize; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.PrevLineSize at the end of BeginTable()
2661 ImVec2 HostBackupCurrLineSize; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.CurrLineSize at the end of BeginTable()
2662 ImVec2 HostBackupCursorMaxPos; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.CursorMaxPos at the end of BeginTable()
2663 ImVec1 HostBackupColumnsOffset; // Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ColumnsOffset at the end of BeginTable()
2664 float HostBackupItemWidth; // Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ItemWidth at the end of BeginTable()
2665 int HostBackupItemWidthStackSize;//Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ItemWidthStack.Size at the end of BeginTable()
2666
2667 ImGuiTableTempData() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); LastTimeActive = -1.0f; }
2668};

2717 // If this ever crash because g.CurrentWindow is NULL it means that either
2718 // - ImGui::NewFrame() has never been called, which is illegal.
2719 // - You are calling ImGui functions after ImGui::EndFrame()/ImGui::Render() and before the next ImGui::NewFrame(), which is also illegal.

2839 // Currently refactoring focus/nav/tabbing system
2840 // If you have old/custom copy-and-pasted widgets that used FocusableItemRegister():
2841 // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM < 18209: using 'ItemAdd(....)' and 'bool tab_focused = FocusableItemRegister(...)'
2842 // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18209: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemAddFlags_Focusable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Focused) != 0'
2843 // (New) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18413: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemFlags_Inputable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_FocusedTabbing) != 0 || g.NavActivateInputId == id' (WIP)
2844 // Widget code are simplified as there's no need to call FocusableItemUnregister() while managing the transition from regular widget to TempInputText()
2845 inline bool FocusableItemRegister(ImGuiWindow* window, ImGuiID id) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); IM_UNUSED(id); return false; } // -> pass ImGuiItemAddFlags_Inputable flag to ItemAdd()
2846 inline void FocusableItemUnregister(ImGuiWindow* window) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); } // -> unnecessary: TempInputText() uses ImGuiInputTextFlags_MergedItem
2847#endif

2952 // Docking - Builder function needs to be generally called before the node is used/submitted.
2953 // - The DockBuilderXXX functions are designed to _eventually_ become a public API, but it is too early to expose it and guarantee stability.
2954 // - Do not hold on ImGuiDockNode* pointers! They may be invalidated by any split/merge/remove operation and every frame.
2955 // - To create a DockSpace() node, make sure to set the ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace flag when calling DockBuilderAddNode().
2956 // You can create dockspace nodes (attached to a window) _or_ floating nodes (carry its own window) with this API.
2957 // - DockBuilderSplitNode() create 2 child nodes within 1 node. The initial node becomes a parent node.
2958 // - If you intend to split the node immediately after creation using DockBuilderSplitNode(), make sure
2959 // to call DockBuilderSetNodeSize() beforehand. If you don't, the resulting split sizes may not be reliable.
2960 // - Call DockBuilderFinish() after you are done.
2961 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderDockWindow(const char* window_name, ImGuiID node_id);
2962 IMGUI_API ImGuiDockNode*DockBuilderGetNode(ImGuiID node_id);
2963 inline ImGuiDockNode* DockBuilderGetCentralNode(ImGuiID node_id) { ImGuiDockNode* node = DockBuilderGetNode(node_id); if (!node) return NULL; return DockNodeGetRootNode(node)->CentralNode; }
2964 IMGUI_API ImGuiID DockBuilderAddNode(ImGuiID node_id = 0, ImGuiDockNodeFlags flags = 0);
2965 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderRemoveNode(ImGuiID node_id); // Remove node and all its child, undock all windows
2966 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderRemoveNodeDockedWindows(ImGuiID node_id, bool clear_settings_refs = true);
2967 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderRemoveNodeChildNodes(ImGuiID node_id); // Remove all split/hierarchy. All remaining docked windows will be re-docked to the remaining root node (node_id).
2968 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderSetNodePos(ImGuiID node_id, ImVec2 pos);
2969 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderSetNodeSize(ImGuiID node_id, ImVec2 size);
2970 IMGUI_API ImGuiID DockBuilderSplitNode(ImGuiID node_id, ImGuiDir split_dir, float size_ratio_for_node_at_dir, ImGuiID* out_id_at_dir, ImGuiID* out_id_at_opposite_dir); // Create 2 child nodes in this parent node.
2971 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderCopyDockSpace(ImGuiID src_dockspace_id, ImGuiID dst_dockspace_id, ImVector<const char*>* in_window_remap_pairs);
2972 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderCopyNode(ImGuiID src_node_id, ImGuiID dst_node_id, ImVector<ImGuiID>* out_node_remap_pairs);
